# Accessibility

**Deep reference:** [franz-frontend skill](../skills/franz-frontend/SKILL.md) → [a11y.md](../skills/franz-frontend/rules/a11y.md).

See also: **`interaction-polish.mdc`**, **`responsive-design.mdc`**, **`shadcn-ui-usage.mdc`**, **`design-tokens.mdc`**, **`theming.mdc`**, **`forms-and-drafts.mdc`**.

Polish without accessibility is incomplete. AI-generated UIs often look fine but fail keyboard, screen reader, and focus management.

## Baseline

- Use **semantic HTML** first (`button`, `nav`, `main`, `label`, `h1`–`h6`).
- Prefer **shadcn/Radix primitives** — focus traps, roles, tabs, dialogs.
- Every interactive control **keyboard operable** (Tab, Enter/Space, Escape).
- **Visible focus** — `ring-ring`; never `outline: none` without replacement (`design-tokens.mdc`).
- **Skip link** — first focusable element in root layout: skip to `#main` (`RootLayout` golden path).

```tsx
<a href="#main" className="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:z-50 focus:p-4 focus:bg-background">
  Skip to main content
</a>
<main id="main">{children}</main>
```

## Labels & names

**A heading is not a label.** Wizard `<h2>` titles do not name inputs — screen readers need an explicit control name.

```tsx
// Bad — visual heading only; Input has no accessible name
<h2>Brand name</h2>
<Input value={name} onChange={...} />

// Good
<h2 id="brand-step-title">Brand name</h2>
<Label htmlFor="brand-name" className="sr-only">Brand name</Label>
<Input id="brand-name" aria-labelledby="brand-step-title" ... />
```

- Every **`Input` / `Textarea` / `Select`** → `<Label htmlFor={id}>` or `aria-label` / `aria-labelledby`.
- **Do not** use `placeholder` as the only label.
- **Icon-only buttons** → `aria-label`; icon `aria-hidden`.

## Tabs & named regions

```tsx
<TabsList aria-label="Content categories">
```

Tab lists, nav landmarks, and grouped controls need a **programmatic name** when visible text alone does not label the group.

## Form errors (RHF + server)

Connect **`aria-invalid`**, **`aria-describedby`**, and error element **`id`** — client Zod and server `fieldErrors` (`api-error-routing.mdc`):

```tsx
const errorId = "website-error";
<Input
  id="website"
  aria-invalid={!!errors.website}
  aria-describedby={errors.website ? errorId : undefined}
/>
{errors.website && (
  <p id={errorId} role="alert" className="text-sm text-destructive">
    {errors.website.message}
  </p>
)}
```

With shadcn `FormField`, use `FormMessage` — it wires describedby when using the Form primitives.

## Dynamic content & live regions

| Event | Pattern |
| ----- | ------- |
| Query loading (region) | `aria-busy="true"` on container |
| **Generating / long mutation** | `role="status"` + `aria-live="polite"` on inline progress — **toasts alone are not enough** |
| Form error summary | `role="alert"` on error text |
| Route change | Focus `h1` or polite live region for title |

```tsx
{isProcessing && (
  <Alert role="status" aria-live="polite">
    <AlertTitle>Processing your request</AlertTitle>
  </Alert>
)}
```

## Keyboard navigation

| Pattern | Requirement |
| ------- | ----------- |
| Dialogs / sheets | Focus trap; `DialogTitle`; Escape closes |
| Menus / dropdowns | Escape; focus returns to trigger |
| Tabs | Arrow keys; named `TabsList` |
| Tables | Row actions not hover-only |

**Do not** rely on `onMouseEnter` as the only path to controls.

## Touch targets

Custom tappable elements must meet **44×44px** — see **`responsive-design.mdc`**.

## Color & motion

- State not conveyed by **color alone** (add text/icon).
- **`prefers-reduced-motion`** — global rule in `index.css` + `interaction-polish.mdc` §22.

## Checklist for PRs

- [ ] Skip link + `<main id="main">` in app shell.
- [ ] Every input has `Label` / `aria-label` / `aria-labelledby` — headings don't count.
- [ ] Errors use `aria-describedby` + `aria-invalid`.
- [ ] Generating/progress states use `aria-live` where visual-only today.
- [ ] `TabsList` and icon buttons have accessible names.
- [ ] Tab-only flow works; dialogs titled.
- [ ] Touch targets ≥ 44×44 on custom controls.
